WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:12.940 --> 00:00:14.670
Inherited will...

3
00:00:14.670 --> 00:00:17.580
the tides of time, and humanity's dreams...

4
00:00:17.580 --> 00:00:20.410
They cannot be stopped.

5
00:00:20.410 --> 00:00:23.520
As long as people seek freedom,

6
00:00:23.520 --> 00:00:26.150
these things will never cease to be.

7
00:00:34.860 --> 00:00:41.080
I only believe in the future -- I don't care if anyone laughs

8
00:00:41.120 --> 00:00:46.600
That racing passion makes you shine

9
00:00:46.620 --> 00:00:52.140
It's too bright, but I want to gaze at it

10
00:00:52.480 --> 00:00:56.120
I sense "aesthetics" somewhere

11
00:00:59.480 --> 00:01:02.740
I follow, follow in the footsteps

12
00:01:02.740 --> 00:01:06.030
of a dream that resembles no one

13
00:01:06.030 --> 00:01:09.260
Until I dramatically get it

14
00:01:18.120 --> 00:01:21.160
I'm going to catch, catch the shape

15
00:01:21.260 --> 00:01:24.240
of a dream no one can see

16
00:01:24.520 --> 00:01:30.260
I'm going to go with you, so passionate feelings

17
00:01:30.500 --> 00:01:33.620
I don't really need everything to add up

18
00:01:33.600 --> 00:01:36.790
Rather than run-of-the-mill daily life,

19
00:01:36.800 --> 00:01:40.390
run for paradise instead

20
00:01:49.960 --> 00:01:53.340
<b>Vivi's Adventure</b>

21
00:01:55.470 --> 00:01:56.760
Bad news!

22
00:02:04.060 --> 00:02:06.690
Where are they, Your Highness?!

23
00:02:07.900 --> 00:02:09.190
What is it, Igaram?

24
00:02:09.190 --> 00:02:10.570
Is something wrong?

25
00:02:10.570 --> 00:02:12.650
Where did Luffy and the others go?

26
00:02:13.030 --> 00:02:14.490
They've gone to sea.

27
00:02:14.490 --> 00:02:15.660
That's what pirates do.

28
00:02:16.200 --> 00:02:17.580
Oh no...

29
00:02:19.540 --> 00:02:20.790
Listen, everyone.

30
00:02:20.160 --> 00:02:23.120
<b>"Turncoat" Jango
Private Third Class
Marine Headquarters</b>

31
00:02:20.790 --> 00:02:23.120
Pirates are absolute scum.

32
00:02:23.120 --> 00:02:25.250
Hey, what're you saying?

33
00:02:24.920 --> 00:02:29.090
<b>"Ironfist" Fullbody
Private Third Class
Marine Headquarters</b>

34
00:02:25.250 --> 00:02:29.090
Did you forget that you used
to be a pirate too?

35
00:02:30.090 --> 00:02:31.420
That's right!

36
00:02:31.420 --> 00:02:33.340
You're exactly right, baby!

37
00:02:33.340 --> 00:02:34.970
Wanna dance?!

38
00:02:34.970 --> 00:02:37.550
Aw, yeah! Dance! Dance!

39
00:02:38.600 --> 00:02:40.350
Dance! Dance!

40
00:02:42.060 --> 00:02:47.360
<b>Nanohana Port
Kingdom of Alabasta</b>

41
00:02:42.930 --> 00:02:45.900
They've returned from
capturing the enemy ship.

42
00:02:45.900 --> 00:02:47.480
Took them long enough.

43
00:02:47.480 --> 00:02:49.280
What were they doing?

44
00:02:49.280 --> 00:02:53.440
And after I entrusted them
with the ship we were attacking...

45
00:02:53.440 --> 00:02:55.740
Hina's disappointed.
Very disappointed.

46
00:02:56.200 --> 00:02:57.780
Have all ships been deployed?

47
00:02:57.780 --> 00:02:59.490
Yes, ma'am! It's perfect!

48
00:02:59.490 --> 00:03:03.120
We've completely blocked
every harbor in the country!

49
00:03:03.120 --> 00:03:04.250
However...

50
00:03:04.910 --> 00:03:07.080
There's just one problem...

51
00:03:07.080 --> 00:03:07.920
What is it?

52
00:03:07.920 --> 00:03:12.640
We had spotted the Straw Hats'
ship in Erumalu but...

53
00:03:12.640 --> 00:03:13.670
it's gone...

54
00:03:13.670 --> 00:03:15.550
Could they have left the country?

55
00:03:15.550 --> 00:03:17.220
No, I doubt that's the case...

56
00:03:17.220 --> 00:03:19.720
Then search along
the entire coast for it!

57
00:03:19.720 --> 00:03:21.140
Yes, ma'am! Will do!

58
00:03:21.140 --> 00:03:22.220
Geez...

59
00:03:22.220 --> 00:03:24.480
Miss Hina! Sorry for the delay!

60
00:03:24.850 --> 00:03:27.060
Aren't you gonna ask
what took us so long?

61
00:03:27.060 --> 00:03:28.480
What took you so long?

62
00:03:28.860 --> 00:03:31.650
– We were picking flowers for you!
– We were picking flowers for you!

63
00:03:30.770 --> 00:03:31.650
Don't need them.

64
00:03:32.150 --> 00:03:35.570
Man your positions! We're going
after the Straw Hat Pirates!

65
00:03:35.570 --> 00:03:37.160
– Th-The Straw Hats?!
– Th-The Straw Hats?!

66
00:03:41.700 --> 00:03:42.700
This is nice.

67
00:03:42.700 --> 00:03:45.120
So it's time to bid
the Kingdom of Sand farewell...

68
00:03:45.120 --> 00:03:46.830
Luffy, you're still eating?

69
00:03:47.170 --> 00:03:49.170
Alabastan food is so yummy!

70
00:03:49.170 --> 00:03:50.920
Sanji, make it sometime!

71
00:03:50.920 --> 00:03:55.800
Yeah. I was interested too, so I got
some recipes and spices from Terracotta.

72
00:03:56.420 --> 00:03:58.470
Nami, are you feeling sick?

73
00:04:00.890 --> 00:04:03.430
Nami, do you want a piece
of meat? Just one, though.

74
00:04:03.770 --> 00:04:06.270
Nami, you're thinking
about Vivi, right?

75
00:04:06.270 --> 00:04:10.650
I know how you feel,
but it's no use brooding.

76
00:04:11.400 --> 00:04:14.150
Yeah, I know you two
were really close...

77
00:04:14.150 --> 00:04:16.610
but hey... cheer up.

78
00:04:17.650 --> 00:04:19.240
For Vivi's sake...

79
00:04:22.580 --> 00:04:24.290
I'll...

80
00:04:24.290 --> 00:04:26.160
give up on...

81
00:04:26.540 --> 00:04:27.620
the billion belly...

82
00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:30.460
– Of course you should!
– Of course you should!

83
00:04:28.790 --> 00:04:30.460
So it was about money?!

84
00:04:30.830 --> 00:04:32.210
Ah! Usopp fell!

85
00:04:32.210 --> 00:04:34.590
Nami! Quit confusing us!

86
00:04:34.590 --> 00:04:36.840
What? What're you guys
so worked up about?

87
00:04:36.840 --> 00:04:39.220
There's no use worrying
about Vivi, right?

88
00:04:39.220 --> 00:04:40.720
Hey! Usopp fell!

89
00:04:40.720 --> 00:04:42.470
Leave him be.

90
00:04:42.470 --> 00:04:44.350
– It was your fault!
– It was your fault!

91
00:04:45.520 --> 00:04:46.560
Karoo!

92
00:04:46.560 --> 00:04:48.020
Where are you, Karoo?!

93
00:04:49.350 --> 00:04:50.940
Don't bother, Igaram.

94
00:04:50.940 --> 00:04:54.610
Why? We should at least inform
them of their current situation.

95
00:04:54.610 --> 00:04:58.360
I had the Supersonic Duck Squad
take them. Karoo wouldn't catch up.

96
00:04:58.360 --> 00:04:59.780
And it won't change anything...

97
00:04:59.780 --> 00:05:01.030
What won't change?

98
00:05:01.030 --> 00:05:05.240
The news would just make them happy.
It won't make any difference.

99
00:05:05.240 --> 00:05:06.080
But...!

100
00:05:06.080 --> 00:05:08.080
They'll be fine!

101
00:05:08.080 --> 00:05:09.710
Now, leave! I'm going to bed!

102
00:05:09.710 --> 00:05:12.080
You have to get up early, right?

103
00:05:12.080 --> 00:05:14.000
Ah... yes. That's right.

104
00:05:14.000 --> 00:05:16.710
You're addressing the entire
kingdom on the morrow.

105
00:05:16.710 --> 00:05:18.590
I know.

106
00:05:18.590 --> 00:05:20.680
Come, Karoo. Let's go to bed.

107
00:05:28.060 --> 00:05:28.980
Igaram.

108
00:05:28.980 --> 00:05:30.140
I have a bad feeling...

109
00:05:30.140 --> 00:05:30.890
What is it?

110
00:05:32.140 --> 00:05:34.150
She's too calm...

111
00:05:35.650 --> 00:05:37.020
Strange...

112
00:05:37.020 --> 00:05:38.610
There's something afoot...

113
00:05:45.200 --> 00:05:47.740
It's quiet, isn't it, Karoo?

114
00:05:49.000 --> 00:05:51.660
We haven't had a quiet night
like this in a long time...

115
00:05:52.080 --> 00:05:56.540
There's no cook fighting
off a fridge thief...

116
00:05:56.540 --> 00:05:59.550
No swordsman training every night...

117
00:05:59.550 --> 00:06:02.680
No navigator throwing
pillows while half asleep...

118
00:06:03.840 --> 00:06:05.640
They're all gone...

119
00:06:09.390 --> 00:06:11.640
A transponder snail call? From who?

120
00:06:11.640 --> 00:06:13.690
Someone named Bon.

121
00:06:13.690 --> 00:06:15.190
Bon? Who's that?

122
00:06:15.190 --> 00:06:16.690
We don't know him.

123
00:06:16.690 --> 00:06:19.530
But he insists he's your friend, so...

124
00:06:19.530 --> 00:06:20.650
Our friend?

125
00:06:21.860 --> 00:06:23.530
Hello?

126
00:06:23.530 --> 00:06:24.740
Hi there!

127
00:06:25.910 --> 00:06:27.070
It's me!

128
00:06:27.070 --> 00:06:28.330
It is m–

129
00:06:31.250 --> 00:06:33.040
What?! Shut up!

130
00:06:34.330 --> 00:06:36.790
Hey, it's you, huh?
What do you want?

131
00:06:36.790 --> 00:06:39.750
Oh? You're Straw Hat, right?

132
00:06:40.130 --> 00:06:43.130
Your strength surprised me!

133
00:06:43.130 --> 00:06:46.510
Oh, yeah... Don't call me Mr. 2.

134
00:06:46.510 --> 00:06:49.640
If the Marines intercept
this call, I'll be in big trouble.

135
00:06:49.640 --> 00:06:51.430
You just said it yourself!

136
00:06:51.430 --> 00:06:52.850
Just get to the point!

137
00:06:52.850 --> 00:06:53.980
Oh, yeah...

138
00:06:53.980 --> 00:06:56.400
I took your ship.

139
00:06:56.400 --> 00:06:57.230
– That's not funny!
– That's not funny!

140
00:06:57.690 --> 00:07:00.230
Cut the jokes, you clown!
Where are you now?!

141
00:07:00.230 --> 00:07:02.230
On your ship!

142
00:07:02.230 --> 00:07:03.900
Of all the people...

143
00:07:03.900 --> 00:07:07.200
Hey, hey, don't be like that!

144
00:07:07.740 --> 00:07:11.660
We're friends, aren't we?

145
00:07:17.380 --> 00:07:20.210
He's up the Sandora River...

146
00:07:20.210 --> 00:07:21.710
Can we trust him?

147
00:07:21.710 --> 00:07:24.090
We were friends back then...

148
00:07:24.090 --> 00:07:26.720
The scary part is you'd
probably befriend him again.

149
00:07:26.720 --> 00:07:28.430
We don't have a choice...

150
00:07:28.430 --> 00:07:30.680
You're right. He has our ship.

151
00:07:30.680 --> 00:07:33.930
If it's a trap, we'll just beat him up.

152
00:07:33.930 --> 00:07:35.730
Alright, let's get ready fast.

153
00:07:35.730 --> 00:07:37.060
Say, everyone...

154
00:07:40.940 --> 00:07:43.440
Say... everyone...

155
00:07:44.940 --> 00:07:46.110
What...

156
00:07:46.860 --> 00:07:49.070
should I do...?

157
00:07:51.450 --> 00:07:53.080
Listen up, Vivi.

158
00:07:53.080 --> 00:07:55.080
We'll give you twelve hours.

159
00:07:54.290 --> 00:08:04.210
<b>Current Location:
Alubarna</b>
<b>Sandora River</b>
<b>Nanohana</b>

160
00:07:55.080 --> 00:07:58.040
Once we take our ship back
on the Sandora River,

161
00:07:58.040 --> 00:08:02.750
we'll make a quick stop by
the eastern port at exactly noon.

162
00:07:59.250 --> 00:08:04.210
<b>Eastern Port</b>

163
00:08:02.750 --> 00:08:04.210
But I doubt we can anchor.

164
00:08:04.840 --> 00:08:07.930
If you wanna keep traveling with us,

165
00:08:07.930 --> 00:08:10.430
that's your one chance
to come aboard.

166
00:08:10.800 --> 00:08:14.680
If you come, we'll welcome you
with open arms as a fellow pirate.

167
00:08:15.020 --> 00:08:19.060
Since you're a princess, this is
the best invitation we can give.

168
00:08:19.060 --> 00:08:21.520
Come on, Vivi! Join us! Right now!

169
00:08:21.520 --> 00:08:23.190
– Stop it, Luffy.
– Let's go.

170
00:08:23.610 --> 00:08:25.860
Why?! Don't you want her to come?!

171
00:08:25.860 --> 00:08:27.450
That's not the point!

172
00:08:27.450 --> 00:08:29.160
Vivi has to decide this herself!

173
00:08:34.330 --> 00:08:36.660
Noon tomorrow...

174
00:08:36.660 --> 00:08:40.420
It takes four hours on Karoo
to get to the eastern port...

175
00:08:40.420 --> 00:08:42.750
I'd have to leave by eight...

176
00:08:43.460 --> 00:08:47.470
Becoming a pirate
never once crossed my mind.

177
00:08:47.470 --> 00:08:53.760
If I miss this chance, I'll never
have another opportunity...

178
00:08:54.720 --> 00:08:57.930
Being a princess
has never been boring...

179
00:08:57.930 --> 00:09:01.600
and this is an important time for
the kingdom, even without a rebellion...

180
00:09:05.360 --> 00:09:07.610
If I leave...

181
00:09:07.610 --> 00:09:09.490
you'll come along, right?

182
00:09:10.650 --> 00:09:11.530
Say...

183
00:09:12.490 --> 00:09:13.700
Karoo...

184
00:09:15.080 --> 00:09:18.250
What... would you like to do?

185
00:09:20.040 --> 00:09:22.670
I've been waiting, you guys!

186
00:09:23.290 --> 00:09:24.790
Long time no see!

187
00:09:25.340 --> 00:09:26.550
We're here!

188
00:09:26.550 --> 00:09:27.920
Okay, unload!

189
00:09:27.920 --> 00:09:29.840
Thanks, ducks!

190
00:09:29.840 --> 00:09:31.720
We have to say goodbye here!

191
00:09:31.720 --> 00:09:32.970
Have a safe trip back!

192
00:09:33.300 --> 00:09:36.180
Say hi to the king, the tube-hair guy,
and everyone for me!

193
00:09:36.180 --> 00:09:37.930
Take care!

194
00:09:37.930 --> 00:09:39.350
We'll...

195
00:09:39.350 --> 00:09:43.730
We'll definitely meet again someday!

196
00:09:45.150 --> 00:09:47.190
Hey, wait a sec!

197
00:09:47.190 --> 00:09:48.030
What?!

198
00:09:48.030 --> 00:09:49.570
Don't "what" me!

199
00:09:49.570 --> 00:09:53.450
Is that any way to treat your friend?!

200
00:09:53.450 --> 00:09:57.200
What do you mean "friend"?
We were enemies! You tricked us!

201
00:09:57.200 --> 00:09:58.910
I didn't trick you!

202
00:09:58.910 --> 00:10:00.660
I didn't know who you were, either!

203
00:10:01.160 --> 00:10:03.870
But what's the point
in worrying about that?

204
00:10:03.870 --> 00:10:05.840
Baroque Works is kaput.

205
00:10:05.840 --> 00:10:08.130
We're not enemies anymo–

206
00:10:08.130 --> 00:10:09.050
Hey, move over.

207
00:10:09.050 --> 00:10:09.880
Oh, sorry.

208
00:10:09.880 --> 00:10:14.090
Even if we're not enemies,
why are you on our ship?!

209
00:10:14.840 --> 00:10:15.890
You stupid head!

210
00:10:15.890 --> 00:10:16.850
What'd you say?!

211
00:10:17.350 --> 00:10:18.180
Listen!

212
00:10:18.180 --> 00:10:22.310
If I wasn't on this ship, deux you
know what would've happened?!

213
00:10:22.690 --> 00:10:24.560
The Marines might have taken it.

214
00:10:24.560 --> 00:10:27.020
What?!
Not "might have"!
They definitely would have!

215
00:10:27.610 --> 00:10:30.150
Deux you know what
they've done around the coast?!

216
00:10:30.150 --> 00:10:32.990
The Marines have it completely
surrounded with ships!

217
00:10:33.360 --> 00:10:37.370
What?! Then you protected
the Going Merry from them?!

218
00:10:37.370 --> 00:10:38.700
– Why?!
– How come?!

219
00:10:40.660 --> 00:10:42.290
Because we're friends!

220
00:10:47.130 --> 00:10:49.170
– Nobody's clowning here!
– Nobody's clowning here!

221
00:10:49.170 --> 00:10:50.300
Is everything loaded?

222
00:10:50.300 --> 00:10:51.800
Yup. This is the last of it.

223
00:10:52.130 --> 00:10:53.970
In other words, Mr. 2...

224
00:10:53.970 --> 00:10:57.930
You couldn't get off the island
because of the Marines' blockade...

225
00:10:57.930 --> 00:11:00.220
so you came to get help, right?

226
00:11:00.220 --> 00:11:01.470
– Bon!
– Bon!

227
00:11:01.970 --> 00:11:05.100
That's right... In a time like this...
No, because it's a time like this...

228
00:11:05.100 --> 00:11:07.270
We must gather
in the name of friendship!

229
00:11:07.270 --> 00:11:09.940
Let us unite our strength
and fight together!

230
00:11:09.940 --> 00:11:14.400
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

231
00:11:13.320 --> 00:11:14.400
Really...?

232
00:11:15.070 --> 00:11:17.910
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

233
00:11:16.700 --> 00:11:17.910
So, thanks in advance!

234
00:11:17.910 --> 00:11:19.620
Your ship was right there?!

235
00:11:20.080 --> 00:11:22.620
Miss Hina! Miss Hina!

236
00:11:22.620 --> 00:11:23.950
We found it!

237
00:11:23.950 --> 00:11:27.080
The Straw Hats' ship is upstream
on the Sandora River!

238
00:11:29.210 --> 00:11:31.130
Prepare to fight.

239
00:11:32.130 --> 00:11:33.920
Igaram, I'm going to...

240
00:11:36.590 --> 00:11:38.590
I'm going to be Queen of the Pirates!

241
00:11:55.990 --> 00:11:58.740
Princess Vivi!

242
00:12:02.040 --> 00:12:03.830
Oh, good morning, Igaram.

243
00:12:03.830 --> 00:12:06.000
Is something wrong?
You're all sweaty.

244
00:12:06.000 --> 00:12:07.290
Hey!

245
00:12:07.290 --> 00:12:09.500
You can't just barge in like that!

246
00:12:09.500 --> 00:12:12.170
Princess Vivi is changing!

247
00:12:13.300 --> 00:12:16.090
Ah... well, um... Good morning.

248
00:12:16.090 --> 00:12:17.550
Yes. So what is it?

249
00:12:17.550 --> 00:12:18.510
Oh, nothing...

250
00:12:18.510 --> 00:12:20.300
Then get out!

251
00:12:20.300 --> 00:12:21.050
Now!

252
00:12:24.850 --> 00:12:27.390
Ow, ow... It truly
was all in my head...

253
00:12:29.690 --> 00:12:32.480
Oh, I didn't notice you,
Your Majesty...

254
00:12:32.480 --> 00:12:33.820
Good morning.

255
00:12:34.190 --> 00:12:36.320
Ah... good morning.

256
00:12:36.320 --> 00:12:39.150
By the way, Terracotta
is quite fearsome, huh?

257
00:12:39.530 --> 00:12:41.620
What were you doing?!

258
00:12:43.910 --> 00:12:46.870
Isn't this too tight, Terracotta?

259
00:12:46.870 --> 00:12:51.460
This is simply how
a princess' formal attire is.

260
00:12:52.210 --> 00:12:54.590
I hear the square is already crowded.

261
00:12:54.590 --> 00:12:55.840
Really?

262
00:12:55.840 --> 00:12:58.840
It was announced that your speech
starts at ten o'clock...

263
00:12:58.840 --> 00:13:00.430
They're so impatient.

264
00:13:01.050 --> 00:13:03.930
Well, I do understand
how they feel, though.

265
00:13:03.930 --> 00:13:06.390
We've waited two extra years for this.

266
00:13:06.890 --> 00:13:08.060
Normally,

267
00:13:08.060 --> 00:13:11.900
your coming-of-age ceremony would
have been held upon turning fourteen.

268
00:13:12.270 --> 00:13:14.900
But I don't have anything
impressive to talk about...

269
00:13:14.900 --> 00:13:16.860
It's okay. You don't need that.

270
00:13:17.610 --> 00:13:21.660
All you have to do is show everyone
how much you've grown. That's it.

271
00:13:21.660 --> 00:13:26.120
The coming-of-age ceremony is held
to celebrate you becoming an adult.

272
00:13:26.120 --> 00:13:31.210
Please consider the king's feelings
in taking the trouble to hold it now.

273
00:13:31.920 --> 00:13:32.960
Oh, yes...

274
00:13:32.960 --> 00:13:36.960
They say your speech will be
broadcast across Alabasta

275
00:13:36.960 --> 00:13:40.220
through transponder
snails and speakers.

276
00:13:40.220 --> 00:13:42.180
I'm looking forward to it.

277
00:13:42.840 --> 00:13:45.220
I received a report
of fighting at the harbor.

278
00:13:45.220 --> 00:13:46.260
I see...

279
00:13:46.260 --> 00:13:50.020
Now that it's come to this,
we can no longer get involved...

280
00:13:51.980 --> 00:13:52.980
Fire!

281
00:13:52.980 --> 00:13:54.480
Fire! Fire!

282
00:13:56.110 --> 00:13:58.030
No fair! Shoot cannonballs, dammit!

283
00:13:58.440 --> 00:14:00.440
Then I could bounce them back!

284
00:14:00.440 --> 00:14:01.610
This is bad!

285
00:14:01.610 --> 00:14:03.490
Nobody's clowning here!

286
00:14:03.490 --> 00:14:07.950
If they keep shooting these iron spears
through our hull, we'll sink in no time!

287
00:14:09.540 --> 00:14:10.540
Incoming!

288
00:14:15.420 --> 00:14:17.710
Hey! I can't keep
plugging these holes!

289
00:14:17.710 --> 00:14:20.170
Do something, you guys!

290
00:14:20.170 --> 00:14:22.930
It takes all our effort
just to protect one side!

291
00:14:25.090 --> 00:14:28.100
Two ships against eight
isn't a fair fight!

292
00:14:28.100 --> 00:14:31.020
If this was close combat,
we'd have a better chance...

293
00:14:32.270 --> 00:14:36.810
Whether we chase or run,
they'll never change this formation!

294
00:14:41.990 --> 00:14:45.240
This is the Black Cage Unit's
trademark black spear formation!

295
00:14:46.740 --> 00:14:50.240
You idiots will never be able
to break it! You're all idiots!

296
00:14:50.240 --> 00:14:52.040
Hey, hypno-guy!

297
00:14:52.040 --> 00:14:53.710
Aren't you a pirate?!

298
00:14:53.710 --> 00:14:54.710
Shut up!

299
00:14:54.710 --> 00:14:57.250
I have my reasons!

300
00:14:57.250 --> 00:14:59.250
Where do I know the guy
on the left from...?

301
00:14:59.250 --> 00:15:01.880
I've finally found them!

302
00:15:01.880 --> 00:15:04.720
That annoying violent
cook and his gang!

303
00:15:05.260 --> 00:15:06.680
Today's the day I sink you!

304
00:15:07.180 --> 00:15:09.180
I've powered up!

305
00:15:09.850 --> 00:15:11.180
Now...

306
00:15:11.180 --> 00:15:13.520
stare at this ring.

307
00:15:13.520 --> 00:15:17.600
Today's the day I finally
prove I'm not a weirdo.

308
00:15:18.810 --> 00:15:19.940
Busy, busy!

309
00:15:20.400 --> 00:15:22.110
One, two...

310
00:15:23.490 --> 00:15:25.280
Jang–

311
00:15:26.700 --> 00:15:27.950
Huh?

312
00:15:27.950 --> 00:15:29.200
Brother!

313
00:15:32.580 --> 00:15:34.080
Whoa...

314
00:15:34.080 --> 00:15:35.660
Usopp! Did you do that?!

315
00:15:35.660 --> 00:15:37.080
Awesome!

316
00:15:37.830 --> 00:15:40.590
Uh... Yeah! All according to plan!

317
00:15:40.590 --> 00:15:42.840
No ship can stand against me!

318
00:15:42.840 --> 00:15:44.590
Nosie, that was amazing!

319
00:15:44.590 --> 00:15:45.840
Good job!

320
00:15:45.840 --> 00:15:49.340
The ships to the south are sunk,
so let's break through while we can!

321
00:15:50.970 --> 00:15:52.430
Mr. Bon Kurei! Bad news!

322
00:15:52.430 --> 00:15:53.430
What is it?!

323
00:15:53.890 --> 00:15:55.350
Black Cage is here!

324
00:15:55.350 --> 00:15:56.230
Oh no!

325
00:15:56.770 --> 00:15:58.270
What's going on?

326
00:15:58.270 --> 00:16:02.110
It's Black Cage Hina, the Marine
captain in charge of this area!

327
00:16:02.520 --> 00:16:04.110
She's a real pain.

328
00:16:04.110 --> 00:16:05.900
Let's hurry and fly the coop!

329
00:16:05.900 --> 00:16:08.320
– Yes, Mr. Bon Kurei!
– Yes, Mr. Bon Kurei!

330
00:16:09.240 --> 00:16:11.240
We've weakened them quite a bit.

331
00:16:11.240 --> 00:16:14.500
No ship can survive
our black spear formation.

332
00:16:14.500 --> 00:16:16.080
Don't get carried away.

333
00:16:16.080 --> 00:16:19.290
You'll end up hurt if you take
guys like them lightly.

334
00:16:20.080 --> 00:16:22.670
Once we pull up, stay back.

335
00:16:22.670 --> 00:16:25.260
If you get in my way,
Hina will be annoyed.

336
00:16:25.260 --> 00:16:26.130
– Yes, ma'am!
– Yes, ma'am!

337
00:16:26.130 --> 00:16:30.050
What're you guys doing?!
We have to run!

338
00:16:30.050 --> 00:16:33.060
We'll take less damage
if we go due south!

339
00:16:33.560 --> 00:16:36.020
If we don't change course,
we'll be sunk for sure!

340
00:16:36.430 --> 00:16:38.940
If you wanna go, then go. We can't.

341
00:16:38.940 --> 00:16:40.980
You can't?! Why?!

342
00:16:40.980 --> 00:16:43.320
Please hurry, Mr. Bon Kurei!

343
00:16:43.320 --> 00:16:45.110
Let's leave them!

344
00:16:45.110 --> 00:16:47.150
We have to be
at the eastern port by noon.

345
00:16:47.150 --> 00:16:48.990
We made a promise.

346
00:16:48.990 --> 00:16:52.120
We won't make it in time
unless we dash through.

347
00:16:53.120 --> 00:16:54.870
That's ludicrous!

348
00:16:54.870 --> 00:16:58.620
Is it some treasure worth
risking your lives over?!

349
00:16:58.620 --> 00:16:59.870
Fine, go die then!

350
00:16:59.870 --> 00:17:01.710
We're gonna pick up a friend.

351
00:17:11.640 --> 00:17:12.260
So...

352
00:17:13.010 --> 00:17:14.760
So it's for your pal...

353
00:17:24.110 --> 00:17:25.940
May I enter, Vivi?

354
00:17:25.940 --> 00:17:27.480
Yes, please do.

355
00:17:28.360 --> 00:17:30.070
What did you wish to talk abo–

356
00:17:30.950 --> 00:17:32.530
Wow...

357
00:17:33.280 --> 00:17:35.370
Remarkable...

358
00:17:35.780 --> 00:17:40.120
Princess Vivi, you're the spitting image
of the queen in her younger days.

359
00:17:40.120 --> 00:17:41.870
Yes, indeed...

360
00:17:42.330 --> 00:17:43.830
Please have a seat, Dadd–

361
00:17:45.380 --> 00:17:46.380
No...

362
00:17:46.380 --> 00:17:48.340
Father and Igaram...

363
00:17:51.090 --> 00:17:53.140
I have something
important to discuss.

364
00:17:53.140 --> 00:17:56.560
– Mr. Bon Kurei!
– Mr. Bon Kurei!

365
00:17:57.810 --> 00:18:00.770
Running now wouldn't
be like Bon Kurei...
"Bon Kurei"

366
00:18:00.770 --> 00:18:01.440
– Huh?!
– Huh?!

367
00:18:01.440 --> 00:18:05.230
If we abandon pals who would
risk their lives to pick up a friend,

368
00:18:05.230 --> 00:18:06.360
how could we...

369
00:18:06.360 --> 00:18:08.190
be able to enjoy our food tomorrow?!

370
00:18:11.900 --> 00:18:13.360
Listen, everyone...

371
00:18:13.360 --> 00:18:15.160
That includes you too, Straw Hats!

372
00:18:17.030 --> 00:18:19.750
Listen carefully to what I have to say!

373
00:18:23.210 --> 00:18:25.830
Miss Hina! They're
dividing their forces!

374
00:18:25.830 --> 00:18:27.460
The duck ship is sailing south!

375
00:18:27.460 --> 00:18:29.340
It's probably a diversion.

376
00:18:29.800 --> 00:18:34.640
Well... Actually, the Straw Hats
are all on the duck ship!

377
00:18:35.050 --> 00:18:37.140
The sheep ship is the decoy!

378
00:18:40.430 --> 00:18:43.390
Follow them! Return to
the formation immediately!

379
00:18:52.400 --> 00:18:53.360
Three minutes!

380
00:18:56.200 --> 00:18:57.370
Prepare to attack!

381
00:18:57.370 --> 00:18:59.410
Ready? Full speed ahead!

382
00:19:01.240 --> 00:19:06.000
Am I this Straw Hat Luffy
you guys are looking for?!

383
00:19:06.710 --> 00:19:07.830
Gotcha!

384
00:19:08.210 --> 00:19:11.090
Miss Hina! The sheep ship
is sailing east!

385
00:19:11.090 --> 00:19:11.800
What?!

386
00:19:16.430 --> 00:19:18.470
You were tricked, weren't you?!

387
00:19:18.470 --> 00:19:21.180
We're masters of disguise!

388
00:19:21.180 --> 00:19:22.640
And also...

389
00:19:25.230 --> 00:19:27.440
friends of the Straw Hats...!

390
00:19:32.940 --> 00:19:35.200
"I can stray from the path of men...

391
00:19:35.200 --> 00:19:37.070
I can stray from the path of women...

392
00:19:37.070 --> 00:19:39.280
but I cannot stray
from the path of mankind!

393
00:19:43.580 --> 00:19:46.670
If we are to fall, we shall descend
together into the true sky.

394
00:19:46.670 --> 00:19:48.790
I will make it bloom!

395
00:19:48.790 --> 00:19:51.750
For that is the okama way!"

396
00:20:00.390 --> 00:20:01.350
By...

397
00:20:01.350 --> 00:20:02.720
Bon Kurei.

398
00:20:10.270 --> 00:20:12.820
Shall we dance?!

399
00:20:14.990 --> 00:20:16.780
Hina's humiliated!

400
00:20:45.100 --> 00:20:46.390
B-Bon!

401
00:20:49.060 --> 00:20:50.310
Bon...

402
00:20:50.310 --> 00:20:51.270
We'll...

403
00:20:58.320 --> 00:21:03.450
We'll never ever forget you!

404
00:21:13.540 --> 00:21:15.460
If we are to fall, let it be in the sea...

405
00:21:15.460 --> 00:21:17.300
Rejoice...

406
00:21:17.920 --> 00:21:19.840
o flower of friendship...

407
00:21:21.840 --> 00:21:23.640
We don't know the ringleader?!

408
00:21:23.640 --> 00:21:26.850
Right... It's a so-called
underground organization.

409
00:21:26.850 --> 00:21:30.230
As for their boss, even its members
know nothing about him.

410
00:21:30.230 --> 00:21:32.400
So that's the enemy of this country...

411
00:21:32.980 --> 00:21:35.980
It's impossible for us
to learn more from the outside.

412
00:21:35.980 --> 00:21:39.320
Rather, further investigation
will only put the country at risk.

413
00:21:39.320 --> 00:21:41.910
But we have a lead, right?

414
00:21:41.910 --> 00:21:42.780
Yes...

415
00:21:42.780 --> 00:21:43.660
Oh?

416
00:21:43.660 --> 00:21:44.450
What?!

417
00:21:45.120 --> 00:21:47.910
Igaram, do you know
what I'm thinking?

418
00:21:47.910 --> 00:21:51.710
N-No! I don't! I-I have
to go back to my work!

419
00:21:51.710 --> 00:21:52.620
Igaram!

420
00:21:52.620 --> 00:21:54.880
No! This isn't a game!

421
00:21:54.880 --> 00:21:57.300
Then that's all the more
reason to, Igaram!

422
00:21:59.130 --> 00:22:01.010
I can't just sit around and do nothing!

423
00:22:16.440 --> 00:22:18.570
They're after us again!

424
00:22:18.570 --> 00:22:20.780
Get out of our way, you bastards!

425
00:22:22.950 --> 00:22:24.490
Look! It's the princess!

426
00:22:24.490 --> 00:22:25.950
Oh, Princess Vivi!

427
00:22:25.950 --> 00:22:27.080
Princess Vivi!

428
00:22:27.080 --> 00:22:28.660
It's Her Highness!

429
00:22:29.200 --> 00:22:31.330
Princess Vivi!

430
00:22:31.330 --> 00:22:33.290
Princess!

431
00:22:33.290 --> 00:22:35.290
She's all grown up!

432
00:22:35.290 --> 00:22:36.210
Your Highness!

433
00:22:36.210 --> 00:22:37.210
Princess Vivi!

434
00:22:37.210 --> 00:22:38.500
Princess!

435
00:22:38.500 --> 00:22:40.380
Princess Vivi!

436
00:22:43.800 --> 00:22:45.470
Then, Princess Vivi...

437
00:22:45.470 --> 00:22:48.680
Let me ask you just one question.

438
00:22:49.310 --> 00:22:51.640
It all started on that day...

439
00:22:52.100 --> 00:22:54.600
Are you resolved to stay alive?

440
00:22:57.310 --> 00:23:01.110
I've been... on a little adventure.

441
00:23:01.110 --> 00:23:03.400
Hey! The princess'
speech has started!

442
00:23:03.400 --> 00:23:04.280
It's been so long!

443
00:23:04.280 --> 00:23:06.070
So she really is okay!

444
00:23:06.070 --> 00:23:07.570
What a relief!

445
00:23:08.070 --> 00:23:10.450
The ceremony in Alubarna has started!

446
00:23:10.450 --> 00:23:12.160
It was delayed by two hours.

447
00:23:12.160 --> 00:23:13.410
What happened?

448
00:23:15.370 --> 00:23:16.920
Well...

449
00:23:16.920 --> 00:23:19.630
I hope it won't cause a commotion...

450
00:23:19.630 --> 00:23:21.760
Koza! Hey, Koza!

451
00:23:21.760 --> 00:23:24.380
Hurry on out!
Vivi's speech has started!

452
00:23:24.380 --> 00:23:27.010
The speakers are cranked
all the way up.

453
00:23:27.010 --> 00:23:29.470
The whole town can hear it.

454
00:23:29.800 --> 00:23:30.890
It was a journey...

455
00:23:31.720 --> 00:23:35.350
A journey of hope
across a sea of despair.

456
00:23:35.350 --> 00:23:38.360
After I left the country,
I saw such a vast ocean.

457
00:23:38.360 --> 00:23:41.570
And on that ocean were
unbelievable, thriving islands...

458
00:23:42.440 --> 00:23:46.820
I saw creatures I'd never imagined
and landscapes out of a dream...

459
00:23:46.820 --> 00:23:48.530
At times, the melody of the waves...

460
00:23:49.030 --> 00:23:54.500
as they swayed gently was quiet
and soothing, easing my worries...

461
00:23:55.540 --> 00:23:57.300
At other times, it was harsh...

462
00:23:57.300 --> 00:24:01.380
laughing at me and trying
to tear apart my weak heart...

463
00:24:04.510 --> 00:24:09.390
But in that dark, dark storm,
I encountered one little ship.

464
00:24:09.890 --> 00:24:12.640
It gave me a push and said...

465
00:24:13.310 --> 00:24:16.600
"Can't you see that light?"

466
00:24:17.810 --> 00:24:22.940
This wondrous ship, which never
lost its way, even in darkness,

467
00:24:22.940 --> 00:24:25.990
danced its way across
the surging waves.

468
00:24:27.200 --> 00:24:34.660
It didn't fight the sea but still sailed
straight ahead even during headwinds.

469
00:24:35.620 --> 00:24:37.870
The ship pointed forward and said...

470
00:24:37.870 --> 00:24:40.630
"Look! There's the light!"

471
00:24:41.460 --> 00:24:44.880
In time, historians
will call this a legend...

472
00:24:45.800 --> 00:24:49.010
but, to me, it is the only truth.

473
00:24:50.010 --> 00:24:52.010
What's she talking about?

474
00:24:52.010 --> 00:24:55.220
It must be her hidden
battle with the Marines.

475
00:24:55.220 --> 00:24:56.220
And...

476
00:25:00.270 --> 00:25:01.980
Vivi...

477
00:25:01.980 --> 00:25:03.980
You hear the speech, right?

478
00:25:03.980 --> 00:25:06.610
That's definitely Vivi's voice.

479
00:25:06.610 --> 00:25:10.110
It's a broadcast
of the ceremony from Alubarna.

480
00:25:10.110 --> 00:25:12.490
She's decided not to come.

481
00:25:12.490 --> 00:25:15.540
No, that just sounded like Vivi!

482
00:25:15.580 --> 00:25:20.210
<b>Eastern Port
Tamarisk</b>

483
00:25:16.330 --> 00:25:18.330
This is that Tamarisk place, right?

484
00:25:18.330 --> 00:25:20.000
Yeah, that's right.

485
00:25:20.870 --> 00:25:22.670
Let's go. It's past noon.

486
00:25:22.670 --> 00:25:24.210
There's no way she's not coming!

487
00:25:24.210 --> 00:25:26.550
Let's go look for her!
She's definitely here!

488
00:25:26.550 --> 00:25:28.050
Hey, bad news!

489
00:25:28.050 --> 00:25:29.840
The Marines are back on our trail!

490
00:25:29.840 --> 00:25:31.510
Just how many ships do they have?!

491
00:25:32.260 --> 00:25:33.640
Dammit! Set sail!

492
00:25:33.640 --> 00:25:35.470
Starboard!

493
00:25:35.970 --> 00:25:37.600
Give it up, Luffy.

494
00:25:37.600 --> 00:25:40.480
She can't just leave everything
behind like we did.

495
00:25:44.230 --> 00:25:46.610
What's going on?

496
00:25:47.360 --> 00:25:49.400
What's the big idea?!

497
00:25:49.440 --> 00:25:53.360
<b>Alubarna</b>

498
00:25:50.400 --> 00:25:53.360
Show your face,
you phony! Or rather...

499
00:25:53.910 --> 00:25:55.450
Commander Igaram!

500
00:25:55.450 --> 00:25:57.620
Where's the real princess?!

501
00:25:57.620 --> 00:26:00.660
Where is the princess' speech
really coming from?!

502
00:26:05.460 --> 00:26:07.880
Her Highness is currently...

503
00:26:08.760 --> 00:26:10.840
Everyone!

504
00:26:22.600 --> 00:26:24.100
Vivi!

505
00:26:24.100 --> 00:26:25.150
Karoo!

506
00:26:28.070 --> 00:26:28.940
Vivi!

507
00:26:28.940 --> 00:26:30.070
See?! She came!

508
00:26:30.070 --> 00:26:31.190
Vivi!

509
00:26:31.190 --> 00:26:33.240
Let's go back! Better hurry!

510
00:26:33.240 --> 00:26:35.320
The Marines are right on our tail!

511
00:26:41.120 --> 00:26:43.120
I came to say goodbye!

512
00:26:45.540 --> 00:26:46.460
What'd she say...?

513
00:26:46.460 --> 00:26:48.090
Karoo, hand me the microphone.

514
00:26:50.670 --> 00:26:52.300
I...

515
00:26:52.300 --> 00:26:54.180
can't go with you!

516
00:26:54.180 --> 00:26:56.300
Thank you so much for everything!

517
00:26:58.220 --> 00:26:59.560
Who is she talking to?

518
00:27:00.010 --> 00:27:02.430
No way... Is that
this country's princess?

519
00:27:02.980 --> 00:27:05.650
She should be at
the ceremony in Alubarna...

520
00:27:05.650 --> 00:27:07.810
I'd like to go on more adventures,

521
00:27:08.400 --> 00:27:12.780
but there's no ignoring...
that I love my country!

522
00:27:12.780 --> 00:27:14.780
Where's Princess Vivi?!

523
00:27:14.780 --> 00:27:16.530
Beat it, Commander Igaram!

524
00:27:16.530 --> 00:27:18.320
We don't wanna see you!

525
00:27:21.200 --> 00:27:23.160
Smooth moves, Commander!

526
00:27:23.160 --> 00:27:24.460
Keep it up!

527
00:27:24.460 --> 00:27:27.630
We came here to see Princess Vivi!

528
00:27:28.880 --> 00:27:31.460
So I can't go!

529
00:27:33.260 --> 00:27:34.220
Got it!

530
00:27:34.590 --> 00:27:35.720
I...

531
00:27:37.640 --> 00:27:39.220
Our sign should be an X!

532
00:27:39.220 --> 00:27:40.180
Why?

533
00:27:40.180 --> 00:27:41.220
We're pirates, right?

534
00:27:41.220 --> 00:27:44.850
But it actually means "death"
to your opponents, you know.

535
00:27:45.350 --> 00:27:47.060
That's fine! I want it to be an X!

536
00:27:47.060 --> 00:27:48.730
It looks cool, right, Vivi?

537
00:27:48.730 --> 00:27:50.650
Yes, I like it, too!

538
00:27:50.650 --> 00:27:54.110
The actual symbol doesn't
matter. Just put something!

539
00:27:58.070 --> 00:27:59.320
I...

540
00:28:03.790 --> 00:28:05.830
I will...

541
00:28:05.830 --> 00:28:07.670
This works!

542
00:28:08.170 --> 00:28:11.670
I will remain here...

543
00:28:12.670 --> 00:28:14.260
Our arms prove we're crewmates!

544
00:28:16.050 --> 00:28:17.970
...but if we ever meet again...

545
00:28:18.970 --> 00:28:22.850
will you still consider me
part of your crew?!

546
00:28:30.900 --> 00:28:34.030
Did you hear that? That princess
is a member of the Straw Hats!

547
00:28:34.030 --> 00:28:36.690
The princess is on
a pirate crew?! No way...!

548
00:28:36.690 --> 00:28:38.030
You'll always be one of u–

549
00:28:37.280 --> 00:28:38.030
Idiot!

550
00:28:39.360 --> 00:28:41.370
Don't reply!

551
00:28:41.370 --> 00:28:43.490
The Marines have noticed her.

552
00:28:44.160 --> 00:28:49.460
If we prove she's connected with us,
they'll brand her a criminal.

553
00:28:50.210 --> 00:28:52.420
Let's part without saying a word.

554
00:29:32.960 --> 00:29:35.250
No matter what happens...

555
00:29:35.250 --> 00:29:39.090
our left arms prove
that we're definitely crewmates!

556
00:30:20.380 --> 00:30:22.840
Set sail!
